NOTES ON RANKING IN 2026
Three things that are doing the heavy lifting in this template:

Specific real-world data — The single biggest differentiator from competitors. AI reviews without numbers get flattened. AI reviews with numbers (even if generated alongside actual driving notes) outrank pure-text generic content.
Named author + credential — Google's helpful content system specifically rewards identifiable expertise. A consistent author with a real bio across all reviews builds topical authority faster than anonymous content.
Honest negatives — Reviews that flag genuine downsides outperform glowing reviews because they match the "balanced perspective" signal Google's quality raters look for. The MCP should be instructed to find at least 2 real complaints from owner forums for every review.